h3cLogicVolume.name: h3cLogicVolume
h3cLogicVolume.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cLogicVolume.description: This MIB describes the general information of disk device.

h3cLvCount.name: h3cLvCount
h3cLvCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of logic volumes supported.

h3cLvMaxSize.name: h3cLvMaxSize
h3cLvMaxSize.description: This object identifies the maximal size of logic volumes supported.

h3cTargetCount.name: h3cTargetCount
h3cTargetCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of targets supported.

h3cInitiatorCount.name: h3cInitiatorCount
h3cInitiatorCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of initiators supported.

h3cSanClientCount.name: h3cSanClientCount
h3cSanClientCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of SAN client supported.

h3cLvCreateIndex.name: h3cLvCreateIndex
h3cLvCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the h3cLvTable object. Reference to h3cLvRowStatus object for more information. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

h3cLvTable.name: h3cLvTable
h3cLvTable.description: This table describes the logic resource information of a logic volume.

h3cLvEntry.name: h3cLvEntry
h3cLvEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular logic resource.

h3cLvIndex.name: h3cLvIndex
h3cLvIndex.description: This object describes the symbol of a logic volume.

h3cLvName.name: h3cLvName
h3cLvName.description: This object identifies the name of a logic volume.

h3cLvTotalSize.name: h3cLvTotalSize
h3cLvTotalSize.description: This object describes the total size of a logic volume. The units is million bytes.

h3cLvCreateRaidUuid.name: h3cLvCreateRaidUuid
h3cLvCreateRaidUuid.description: This object describes the ID of array where a logic volume build on.

h3cLvCreateRaidSize.name: h3cLvCreateRaidSize
h3cLvCreateRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of a logic volume when create it. The units is million bytes.

h3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep.name: h3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep
h3cLvSedInquiryStringKeep.description: This object identifies if the inquiry string of the logic volume should be reserved. This value of this object is valid only when the associated h3cLvType is equal to 'serviceEnabled'.

h3cLvSedRaidUuid.name: h3cLvSedRaidUuid
h3cLvSedRaidUuid.description: This object describes the location where the SED infomation is build on.

h3cLvState.name: h3cLvState
h3cLvState.description: This object identifies the state of a logic volume. The value 'conflict' means the names of two or more logic volume are reduplicate.

h3cLvAssigned.name: h3cLvAssigned
h3cLvAssigned.description: This object identifies if the logic volume has be designated for target or SAN client.

h3cLvType.name: h3cLvType
h3cLvType.description: This object describes the type of a logic volume. The value 'virtual' means virtual devices are defined as sets of storage blocks from one or more physical array. This allows the creation of virtual devices that can be a portion of a larger physical array, or an aggregation of multiple physical array. The value 'direct' means direct devices are directly mapped SCSI devices. Because they are not virtualized, direct devices cannot take advantage of advanced storage options, such as mirroring, failover, replication, or snapshot copy. The value 'serviceEnabled' means service enabled devices are all maintained in a one-to-one mapping relationship(one physical array equals one logical device).

h3cLvExtendTimes.name: h3cLvExtendTimes
h3cLvExtendTimes.description: This object describes the times the logic volume has been extended.

h3cLvRowStatus.name: h3cLvRowStatus
h3cLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to create or delete a logic volume.

h3cLvExtTable.name: h3cLvExtTable
h3cLvExtTable.description: This table contains the extend resource information of the logic volume.

h3cLvExtEntry.name: h3cLvExtEntry
h3cLvExtEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to extend resource of logic volume.

h3cLvRaidUuid.name: h3cLvRaidUuid
h3cLvRaidUuid.description: This index is identical to h3cRaidUuid in H3C-RAID-MIB.

h3cLvExtSize.name: h3cLvExtSize
h3cLvExtSize.description: This object describes the extend size of the logic volume in a specific raid. The units is million bytes. This object will always return zero when read.

h3cLvRaidSize.name: h3cLvRaidSize
h3cLvRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of logic volume on the specific raid. The units is million bytes.

h3cLvExtRowStatus.name: h3cLvExtRowStatus
h3cLvExtRowStatus.description: This object describes the action to extend the logic volume.

h3cTargetCreateIndex.name: h3cTargetCreateIndex
h3cTargetCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the h3cTargetTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

h3cTargetTable.name: h3cTargetTable
h3cTargetTable.description: This table describes some information when creating a target.

h3cTargetEntry.name: h3cTargetEntry
h3cTargetEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a target when create it.

h3cTargetId.name: h3cTargetId
h3cTargetId.description: This object identifies the ID of a target.

h3cTargetName.name: h3cTargetName
h3cTargetName.description: This object describes the name of a target.

h3cTargetMinLun.name: h3cTargetMinLun
h3cTargetMinLun.description: This object describes the mini LUN(logical unit number) number of a target.

h3cTargetRowStatus.name: h3cTargetRowStatus
h3cTargetRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the target.

h3cTargetAddressTable.name: h3cTargetAddressTable
h3cTargetAddressTable.description: This table described some address information of a target.

h3cTargetAddressEntry.name: h3cTargetAddressEntry
h3cTargetAddressEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the address of a target.

h3cTargetIpAddress.name: h3cTargetIpAddress
h3cTargetIpAddress.description: This object describes the IP address of a target.

h3cTargetIpAddrType.name: h3cTargetIpAddrType
h3cTargetIpAddrType.description: This object describes the type of IP address.

h3cTargetIpRowStatus.name: h3cTargetIpRowStatus
h3cTargetIpRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete a IP address of a target.

h3cTargetLvAssignTable.name: h3cTargetLvAssignTable
h3cTargetLvAssignTable.description: This table describes logic resource information of a target.

h3cTargetLvAssignEntry.name: h3cTargetLvAssignEntry
h3cTargetLvAssignEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the logic resource of a target.

h3cTargetLvLun.name: h3cTargetLvLun
h3cTargetLvLun.description: This object identifies the init LUN number of a target.

h3cTargetLvRowStatus.name: h3cTargetLvRowStatus
h3cTargetLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the logic resource of a target.

h3cInitiatorCreateIndex.name: h3cInitiatorCreateIndex
h3cInitiatorCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the h3cInitiatorTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

h3cInitiatorTable.name: h3cInitiatorTable
h3cInitiatorTable.description: This table describes the creation information of initiators.

h3cInitiatorEntry.name: h3cInitiatorEntry
h3cInitiatorEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the creation of initiator.

h3cInitiatorId.name: h3cInitiatorId
h3cInitiatorId.description: This object identifies the ID of the initiator.

h3cInitiatorName.name: h3cInitiatorName
h3cInitiatorName.description: This object describes the name of the initiator.

h3cInitiatorRowStatus.name: h3cInitiatorRowStatus
h3cInitiatorRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete initiators.

h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable.name: h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable
h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateTable.description: This table describes the associate information between the target and initiator.

h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry.name: h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry
h3cTargetInitiatorAssociateEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to association between the target and initiator.

h3cTIAccessMode.name: h3cTIAccessMode
h3cTIAccessMode.description: This object identifies the mode of accessing between the target and initiator. The value 'read' means read available. The value 'write' means read/write available, and write available only for one association. The value 'nonexclusive' means read/write available for multi-association.

h3cTIChap.name: h3cTIChap
h3cTIChap.description: This object identifies the state of the chap attestation.

h3cTIUserName.name: h3cTIUserName
h3cTIUserName.description: This object identifies the user name for the chap attestation.

h3cTIPassword.name: h3cTIPassword
h3cTIPassword.description: This object identifies the password for the chap attestation. It is proclaimed and can be modified.

h3cTIRowStatus.name: h3cTIRowStatus
h3cTIRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the association.

h3cTISessionTable.name: h3cTISessionTable
h3cTISessionTable.description: This table described the information of the sessions.

h3cTISessionEntry.name: h3cTISessionEntry
h3cTISessionEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the sessions.

h3cTISessionId.name: h3cTISessionId
h3cTISessionId.description: This object identifies the ID of a session.

h3cTISessionConnectionCount.name: h3cTISessionConnectionCount
h3cTISessionConnectionCount.description: This object describes the number of connections between the targets and initiators.

h3cTISessionInitiatorName.name: h3cTISessionInitiatorName
h3cTISessionInitiatorName.description: This object identifies the initiator's name of a session.

h3cSanClientCreateIndex.name: h3cSanClientCreateIndex
h3cSanClientCreateIndex.description: This object supplys an valid index which uses to create a new entry for the h3cSanClientTable object. Note that if an entry of the associated table has been created or deleted, the historical value of this object may be an invalid index to create a new entry for the associated table.

h3cSanClientTable.name: h3cSanClientTable
h3cSanClientTable.description: This table described the information of SAN(Storage Area Network) clients.

h3cSanClientEntry.name: h3cSanClientEntry
h3cSanClientEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the SAN clients.

h3cSanClientId.name: h3cSanClientId
h3cSanClientId.description: This object identifies the index of a SAN client.

h3cSanClientName.name: h3cSanClientName
h3cSanClientName.description: This object identifies the name of a SAN client.

h3cSanClientType.name: h3cSanClientType
h3cSanClientType.description: This object identifies the type of a SAN client.

h3cFcInitiatorWwpnList.name: h3cFcInitiatorWwpnList
h3cFcInitiatorWwpnList.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Initiator WWPN(World Wide Port Name). The value of this object is invalid and should be ignored when the value of associated h3cSanClientType object is not equal to 'fc'.

h3cFcAccessMode.name: h3cFcAccessMode
h3cFcAccessMode.description: This object identifies the mode of access. The value of this object is invalid and should be ignored when the value of associated h3cSanClientType object is not equal to 'fc'. The value 'read' means read available. The value 'write' means read/write available, and write available only for one association. The value 'nonexclusive' means read/write available for multi-association.

h3cSanClientRowStatus.name: h3cSanClientRowStatus
h3cSanClientRowStatus.description: This object describes the action to create or delete a SAN client.

h3cFcLogicResourceTable.name: h3cFcLogicResourceTable
h3cFcLogicResourceTable.description: This table describes logic resource information of a FC.

h3cFcLogicResourceEntry.name: h3cFcLogicResourceEntry
h3cFcLogicResourceEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the logic resource of a FC.

h3cFcLvLun.name: h3cFcLvLun
h3cFcLvLun.description: This object identifies the init LUN number of a FC.

h3cFcTargetWwpnName.name: h3cFcTargetWwpnName
h3cFcTargetWwpnName.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Target WWPN(World Wide Port Name).

h3cFcInitiatorWwpnName.name: h3cFcInitiatorWwpnName
h3cFcInitiatorWwpnName.description: This object identifies the name list of FC Initiator WWPN(World Wide Port Name).

h3cFcLvRowStatus.name: h3cFcLvRowStatus
h3cFcLvRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to add or delete the logic resource of a FC.
